TopicTitle: KASDA mission log | Y108, D327 | Endgame: escaping Eve, conclusion (FINAL MISSION)

Articles.Content:
Mission 261: Kinsei Maru + Tsubu Base (MIKU-43) + Song Princess 23a/b/c + 24a/b/c

Eve system colony ship, Gilly base, and comsats for both bodies. Since the first interplanetary crewed missions, KASDA has neglected settling Gilly in favor of Duna and the planets and moons further beyond, as well as Moho. But finally, Kerbals will live on Eve's moon. (97794 kg launch mass, K-3 launch vehicle)

Mission 262:  Negi Star Mk2 flight 20

Mission 269: Negi Star Mk2 flight 22

Camlorf Kerman, who landed on Slate (Sarnus's largest moon) in the past, will become the first Kerbal on Eve. Joayne, Megcee, Jenfrey, Megelyn, Orfurt, Patgan, Algy, and Gerlorf Kerman will go along for the ride to study the planet from a low orbit. (K-1b launch vehicle)

Mission 270: Project DIVA X 5th / Negi Maru flight 08 (part 1, part 2, part 3, part 4)

Designing Interplanetary Vehicle Architecture with eXtreme-efficiency propulsion, 5th mission. The final mission of the Negi Maru (and this series), to accomplish the hardest task of any Kerbal space agency: putting a Kerbal on Eve and not stranding them there. We're in the endgame now.

(Yes, Eve is Thanos Planet.)

Mission 270: Project DIVA X 5th / Negi Maru flight 08 (part 1, part 2, part 3, part 4)

Designing Interplanetary Vehicle Architecture with eXtreme-efficiency propulsion, 5th mission. Arriving at and landing on Eve.

Y107, D421 (Negi Maru Eve insertion)
Y107, D422 (Eve Rabbit 1 landing)

(note: temporarily removed Stock Visual Enhancements, leaving Environmental Visual Enhancements and Scatterer, as Eve's sky was pitch black otherwise)

Camlorf Kerman on the surface of Eve, feeling 1.7 times as heavy as he does on Kerbin (808 m altitude)

Spoiler

Combined orbital insertion maneuver and plane change at over 9000 km

Lowering to a ~145 km orbit over three burns

Camlorf makes an EVA to the lander's command pod

De-orbit burn using a braking stage

Atmospheric entry, stabilized by two inflatable heat shields

Once the speed dropped to a low enough level, the upper heat shield detached, parachutes were deployed, then the lower shield detached.

With the parachutes and Eve's thick atmosphere, descent was around 14 m/s. Five vector engines fired at the last few moments to slow to a safe landing speed.

Camlorf climbing down the ladder

 

Edited August 28, 2020 by Pipcard
Man... this is it. One. Last. Report.

Mission 270: Project DIVA X 5th / Negi Maru flight 08 (part 1, part 2, part 3, part 4)

Designing Interplanetary Vehicle Architecture with eXtreme-efficiency propulsion, 5th mission. Returning from the very deep gravity well that is Eve's surface.

Y107, D426 (Eve Rabbit 1 liftoff)

Soundtrack:

Liftoff on the last day of the year

Spoiler

Camlorf waited a full Eve day (3 Kerbin days + 4 hours =  22 hours) before launching

Detaching science payload

Jettisoning landing legs

The four liquid rocket boosters used asparagus staging, and were meant to give the initial high thrust needed in the thick lower atmosphere.

Once the second pair of boosters had detached, the main core stage initially did not have a high enough thrust-to-weight ratio.

But as propellant was burned and the vehicle got higher, the TWR would increase such that throttling down was necessary to prevent overheating.

Upper stage activated [at this point I realized that I left the antenna open, so I closed it]

Powered by a single Terrier engine, it would provide the final boost to orbit.

Orbit achieved (with plenty of Delta-v to spare)! Eve had finally been conquered.

Rendezvous with the Negi Maru and Camlorf's EVA back to the ship

Kerbals had now set foot on every solid body in the Kerbol system. Now the only thing left to do was to wait and return home.
